Reasoning: The paper deals with the representation and evaluation of continuous functions, which involves computational complexity and algorithms. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the speed of evaluation, which could fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation). Finally, the paper involves proving the minimality of a representation, which could be related to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
